# Lab: Group Weekend Routine Plans

> It is Friday and two classmates are planning what their group will do this weekend using the same routine sequence.

## Roles

A: Persona 1
  You lead a group weekend plan and check details

B: Persona 2
  You describe your family/group plan and compare it

## Turns

A: Ask about their group weekend plan
   (Open with plural)
   - Que van a hacer este fin de semana? | What are you all going to do this weekend?
   hint: Hola! Que van a hacer en familia este fin de semana?

B: Start your sequence with levantarse and desayunar
   (Use nos vamos a / vamos a)
   - Nos vamos a levantar... | We are going to get up...
   - Luego vamos a desayunar... | Then we are going to have breakfast...
   hint: Nos vamos a levantar temprano y luego vamos a desayunar juntos.

A: Ask about work, exercise, and lunch
   (Prompt ellos/ellas)
   - Ellos van a trabajar? | Are they going to work?
   - Ellas van a hacer ejercicio? | Are they going to exercise?
   - Y ustedes van a almorzar juntos? | And are you all going to have lunch together?
   hint: Despues ellos van a trabajar, ellas van a hacer ejercicio y ustedes van a almorzar?

B: Answer with working block
   (Use group forms and one yo naturally)
   - Ellos van a trabajar... | They are going to work...
   - Ellas van a hacer ejercicio... | They are going to exercise...
   - Vamos a almorzar... | We are going to have lunch...
   hint: Si, ellos van a trabajar por la manana, ellas van a hacer ejercicio por la tarde y vamos a almorzar al mediodia. Yo voy a cocinar.

A: Ask how they will finish the day
   (Move to night)
   - Y por la noche que van a hacer? | And what are you all going to do at night?
   - Van a cenar en casa? | Are you all going to have dinner at home?
   hint: Y por la noche van a cenar, ver la tele y dormir temprano?

B: Close with cenar, ver la tele, dormir
   (Complete with vamos a + one yo line)
   - Vamos a cenar... | We are going to have dinner...
   - Vamos a ver la tele... | We are going to watch TV...
   - Vamos a dormir... | We are going to sleep...
   hint: Vamos a cenar a las ocho, ver la tele un rato y dormir temprano. Yo voy a cerrar la cocina.

A: Invite them to match plans
   (Finish together)
   - Quieren hacer el mismo plan? | Do you all want to do the same plan?
   - Nos vemos el sabado! | See you Saturday!
   hint: Perfecto. Quieren hacer el mismo plan con nosotros el sabado?

## Tips

- Prioritize `vamos a` and `van a` for group planning; include `voy a` naturally in one detail.
- Keep the same sequence: levantarse, desayunar, trabajar, hacer ejercicio, almorzar, cenar, ver la tele, dormir.
- Repeat connectors (despues, luego, por la noche) so your plan sounds organized.
